                    	<note xml:id="n_dating" type="dating">
                    	    
<p xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance">Van Gogh wrote this letter the day after sending a consignment of paintings <ref target="#l-25">(ll. 25-26)</ref>. Since the consignment was sent on 3 January, we have dated the letter to Saturday, 4 January 1890. Cf. also <hi rend="italics">Additional details</hi>.</p>
                    	</note>
                    
                    
                    
                    	<note xml:id="n_remarks" type="remarks">
                    	    
                                    
<p xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance">Because the letter was written on the same day as <ref target="let836.xml">letter 836</ref> to Theo, and Willemien was then staying with Theo and Jo, it is likely that the two letters were sent together. </p>
                                    
                                
                    	</note>
                    
